# Task Completion Summary

**Task:** 02_audio_pipeline
**Completed At:** 2026-02-28T13:13:00+01:00
**Mode:** Code

## Results

Implemented the full audio capture pipeline directly within the renderer process using `getUserMedia`, an `AudioWorkletNode`, and `@ricky0123/vad-web`. When speech stops, the captured PCM buffer is encoded to an array buffer format equivalent to a WAV file (16-bit, 16kHz, mono) and chunked to the main process via IPC. A local copy of the Silero ONNX models has been configured to ensure offline availability.

## Files Created/Modified

- `src/renderer/audio/mic-capture.js` - `getUserMedia` logic and `AudioWorklet` connection
- `src/renderer/audio/vad.js` - Wrapper for Silero VAD implementation
- `src/renderer/audio/audio-processor.worklet.js` - The worklet for feeding Float32 chunks downstream
- `src/renderer/audio/wav-encoder.js` - PCM to WAV chunk encoder
- `src/renderer/index.js` - Wired up recording toggles
- `src/shared/constants.js` - `AUDIO_CHUNK` IPC channel
- `src/main/preload.js` - Exposed `sendAudioChunk()` in specific context map

